# Stack Rules

## Package Manager
- Always use `pnpm` as the package manager
- Use `pnpm install` instead of `npm install` or `yarn install`
- Reference `pnpm` commands in documentation and scripts

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Follow Tailwind's utility-first approach
- Use Tailwind classes instead of custom CSS when possible
- Import Tailwind in styles.css with `@import "tailwindcss"`
- Leverage Vocs CSS variables for theming: `var(--vocs-color_*)`
- Use responsive design patterns with Tailwind breakpoints

## Documentation Framework
- Use Vocs for documentation generation
- Structure content in `docs/pages/` directory using MDX files
- Configure via `vocs.config.ts` in project root
- Use file-based routing for documentation pages
- Place static assets in `docs/public/` directory
- Implement proper SEO with:
  - Descriptive page titles using `titleTemplate`
  - Meta descriptions via `description` config
  - Open Graph images with `ogImageUrl`
  - Proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
  - Semantic HTML structure

## Code Examples Generation
- Use `@generate-mdx-examples.js` script to auto-generate code examples
- Import generated examples in MDX files for consistency
- Keep examples in sync with actual test files
- Generate examples from test files to ensure accuracy
- Use proper syntax highlighting with language tags
- Include GitHub source links in generated examples